1. Create a set of unvisited nodes and initialize the distance of the source node to 0 and all other nodes to infinity.

2. Select the node with the smallest distance (initially the source node) and mark it as visited. Update the distances of its neighbors. If the new distance is less than the current distance, update the distance.

3. Repeat step 2 until all nodes are visited or the target node is visited.

